<br />

<h2 class="pen"><a rel="bookmark" https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?id=980" title="Permanent link to this article">Now doing the floor</a></h2>

<div class="post">

<div class="entrytext">

	<p>Improvements are once again starting to occur at the Mudcat Building.</p>

	<p>About two years ago we replaced the roof on our building&#8217;s warehouse annex. It should have been replaced 20 years ago. Water was pouring through it so bad, it might as well been without a roof entirely.</p>

	<p>The flooring was similarly shot by having water pour down. Now, two years later, we&#8217;re attacking the floor.</p>

	<p>Yesterday we took out the extraneous layers of OSB fiberboard in order to get down to the original flooring. We hoped the bottom layer would be in good enough shape to simply build on top of it. However, it too was pretty well shot so then we pulled up all the boards on half the floor. This exposed the beams, a couple of which are covered with mushrooms. We&#8217;ll replace those too <strong>sigh</strong></p>

	<p>We had to drag all that wood out of the warehouse and then get it cut up so our friend could use it as firewood this winter. This was an exhausting process, but it beats having to pay for a dumpster.</p>

	<p>I managed to work eight hours without hurting myself (which I rarely do anymore, but I still live with the alleged reputation of getting hurt in weird ways). I&#8217;m rather sore this morning, but what should I expect?</p>

	<p>We&#8217;ll post photos as soon as I manage to get them out of the camera. It&#8217;s a rather impressive looking space. In New York City, the loft alone would go for a cool million easily. Mind you this is Madison.</p>

	<p>This is a keystone project for us. Finishing this will allow us to upgrade the electric and expand Darlene&#8217;s studio. Very good things as a specific recently imprisoned person might say.</p>



 

<p class="postmetadata alt">

<small>This entry was posted on Oct 10 by <a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?author=E.G.+Yarnetsky">E.G. Yarnetsky</a>. You can skip to the end and leave a response using the comment form.</small></p>

</div>

</div>




	

